Input.question: A town between two mountains is located in a what?
Input.answer_choices: michigan, valley, state, hospital, or train station
Input.explanation_1: Because all of the mountains are to the left of this town, if one was looking on a map, one would be able to see the town in the valley.
Input.explanation_2: A valley is usually between two mountains, where it is located in the place where the mountains are closest to each other.
Input.explanation_3: Because rivers end in valleys; assuming the river is the one of interest, this sentence is likely referring to the geographical location of the town.
Input.explanation_4: A town in between mountains presumably would be in a valley, in which case it is plausable that it would be surrounded by heights in every direction.
Input.explanation_5: A valley is a low area between two mountains.

Input.question: Where would there be an auditorium with only a single person speaking?

Input.explanation_3: Stroking a dog's fur makes the dog happy, which would please the owners of the dog.
Input.explanation_4: Stroking a dog's fur is a way of petting it, and petting a dog is a way of giving it attention.
Input.explanation_5: Stroking dogs often garners attention and affection, whereas picking dogs can cause them to start fighting.

Input.question: What does everyone have in relation to other people?
Input.answer_choices: different standards, values, feelings, unique personality, or food
Input.explanation_1: Without basic feelings like hunger, love, guilt, or anger, people could hardly interact with any other person. Each person necessarily has these feelings.
Input.explanation_2: Everyone has feelings, which are subjective and unique to each person.
Input.explanation_3: Other things can be different with people, but shared shared feelings are something that everyone will have in common. Like glee.
Input.explanation_4: Feelings are a characteristic of every living being, whereas the other options aren't common to all organisms. Some organisms produce no food, but higher organisms must consume food. Feelings, however, may exist in any organism.
Input.explanation_5: Feelings and emotions pervade the cultures around the world. Many factors help shape someone's feelings. One human's feelings are different from another's.

Input.question: The lock kept the steering wheel from moving, but the thief still took his chances and began to work on the what?
Input.answer_choices: ignition switch, train, firearm, drawer, or keep cloesd
Input.explanation_1: Vehicle theft can be difficult, as it may require some general mechanical knowledge of the vehicle. But the ignition switch of the vehicle is not as difficult to bypass as say, some other component, or as getting a new ignition device from some black market store
Input.explanation_2: Steering wheels are not used to start cars, so the thief was most likely interested in getting into the car to take something valuable, but not with opening the doors. During this process, the steering wheel does not need to be locked.
Input.explanation_3: The steering wheel and the ignition switch operate different parts of a car: the steering wheel is connected to the tires, while the ignition switch starts the vehicle.
Input.explanation_4: The ignition switch prevents the car from being moved, but the thief took the car by driving it, e.g., driving off without the key.
Input.explanation_5: The ignition switch is the part of the car that starts the engine. If the thief could not start the engine, he would not be able to drive away with the car.

Input.question: Before racers start to run they must do what at the starting line?
Input.answer_choices: stand still, walking, breathe, learn to walk, or walk slowly
Input.explanation_1: Before starting to run, a runner must take their starting position.
Input.explanation_2: If racers begin to run while they're at rest at the starting line, they won't get anywhere!
Input.explanation_3: Before racers start to run, they must stand still at the starting line.
Input.explanation_4: Racers" who compete may do all sorts of things before races such as warming up, stretching, and stretching cognitively. Learning to walk is a famous example of an ontogenetic development.
Input.explanation_5: Suppose runners start before the starting horn blows; can we really say they actually started right before the horn? Rules of the race generally demand that the entire running community waits for the starting horn.

Input.question: James was someone who was caught in his own delusions.  To him, the truth didn't do what what?
Input.answer_choices: matter to, help, free mind, further knowledge, or work to advantage
Input.explanation_1: The truth can sometimes be painful. If your delusions "don't matter to you," then you might not be as concerned with the truth as you would be.
Input.explanation_2: The truth according to James might not matter because in his delusions, his view of truth is there in order to help in some way.
Input.explanation_3: People in denial tend to ignore facts that contradict their views. If facts matter to someone, that means facts work to that person's advantage. If facts do not matter, then facts work to no one's advantage.
Input.explanation_4: People in delusions shouldn't look to the truths (facts) because the truths might dispell the delusions to which they hold.
Input.explanation_5: If you are delusional, the truth may not matter to you.

Input.question: If you turn off the music in a room with no other noise that room would be what?
Input.answer_choices: silence, opera, elevator, silent, or television
Input.explanation_1: With no other noise sources, e.g., music playing, an elevator beeping repeatedly, or a blender, the room would be silent. This is not the case if there is someone speaking or an opera song playing.
Input.explanation_2: If there is no other noise in a room, then the room would be silent.
Input.explanation_3: Assume you turn off the music in a room; because there is no other noise (e.g., speaker vibration, other people talking, etc.), you would experience silence. Silence therefore refers to the absence of external noise.
Input.explanation_4: If you were in a room with no outside noise, there would be no noise in the room. This means there would be silence.
Input.explanation_5: Although television has some noise involved, when the TV is turned off people in the room will generally emit enough chatter to make the room generally quiet.

Input.explanation_3: When you don't allow peace officers to block justice, peace officers are seprone to use certain kinds of brutally force.
Input.explanation_4: Police improperitory is reviewed by prosecutors before being tried in court, not in the street where people tend to get injured when police officers use violence in their duties.
Input.explanation_5: Cops who use anti-protest tactics to disrupt legal demonstrations often have those tactics backfire on them, as those same protestors turn around and attack the police; because of this police tactics, protestors often get hurt.

Input.question: Where would using a boat not require navigation skills?
Input.answer_choices: garage, water, river, harbor, or ocean
Input.explanation_1: If one were using a boat that floated on the current of a river, one would not need skills for navigating because, for at least some part of their journey, the winds would guide them naturally.
Input.explanation_2: Boats tend to carry people relatively short distances by using rivers. People who navigate their way up rivers only require the knowledge of the geography of the regions.
Input.explanation_3: Boats are often used on rivers, and rivers are often used for transportation. Navigation skills are not required for this.
Input.explanation_4: John may find it more difficult to navigate a boat on the ocean, b/c he is unfamiliar with the locations of things on the ocean. Using a boat on a river would more easily give him access to locations he is already familiar with.
Input.explanation_5: often there is some sort of boat house nearby where a boat could be left, and so there is typically no need to navigate back to where you left it.

Input.question: If you're celebrating with too many cocktails what may you have in the morning?
Input.answer_choices: have fun, intimacy, drunkenness, hang over, or headache
Input.explanation_1: After a long night or night of drinking, one's head or stomach might feel ill the next day, often being referred to as a "hangover.
Input.explanation_2: Hang overs happen after many drinks, and can result in headaches and nausea, making it hard to work on some levels.
Input.explanation_3: Alcohol may cause someone to feel sick and/or headache-y if they have drank too much and were drunk the night before. These feelings and sickness might interfere with their ability to wake up and enjoy non-hangover-y activities.
Input.explanation_4: If you drink too much alcohol, you may wake up with a hangover, which is a headache caused by drinking too much alcohol.
Input.explanation_5: people may celebrate with alcoholic beverages, but if they exceed the drink maximum they will suffer the following morning; this might make them hung over, which commonly effects the brain more than the body.

Input.question: If you want to learn about the world and understand the real reasons behind cultural norms and mores, you have achieved a sense of what?
Input.answer_choices: confusion, enlightenment, anger, open mind, or smartness
Input.explanation_1: Enlightenment is the state of being enlightened, which is the state of having an open mind, which is the state of being smart.
Input.explanation_2: Studying cultural norms and mores, via books or otherwise, can help you gain a "sense of Enlightenment", aka, an understanding of what may have seemed mysterious to you before.
Input.explanation_3: Enlightenment is achieved after learning about cultural norms, cultural reasons for cultural norms, the human condition, the human experience, and so on.
Input.explanation_4: The pursuit of asking questions about everything can help to create an "enlightened" state of mind, wherein the person is willing to learn about how the world works, instead of simply accepting what people expect/feed them.
Input.explanation_5: People who achieve sense of enlightenment are more commonly known as smart people, and their greater intelligence comes from weighing and considering multiple points of view and adopting change.

Input.question: To what do trees roots cling?
Input.answer_choices: countryside, surface of earth, museum, orchard, or yard
Input.explanation_1: Tree roots cling to the ground in order to get a secure foundation to send vertical roots towards water and nutrients.
Input.explanation_2: Roots are attached to the surface of the earth, and so if a tree was uprooted, it would likely be in a countryside.
Input.explanation_3: Trees need to be firmly affixed to something in order to grow. While it could be the edge of the farm, it is more likely to be the surface of the Earth, which is made of dirt or rock, but not stone or metal.
Input.explanation_4: The location of tree roots is fixed to the surface of the earth.
Input.explanation_5: In the natural world, the earth provides a firm substrate for plants' roots to hold on. In a greenhouse, plants do not have as much surface as they need, so they must be kept in pots or anchored with string, cloth, or plastic

Input.question: Where would you find a fox that is made up?
Input.answer_choices: woods, storybook, back yard, hen house, or natural habitat
Input.explanation_1: A fox that is made up is often kept as a pet, and could be kept in people's backyards or hen houses.
Input.explanation_2: A fox that is made up is a fictional fox, and so it is likely to be found in a storybook.
Input.explanation_3: Pets that are kept indoors will typically have little contact with other types of animals, and so may be said to be "made up". For educational purposes, an educator who writes a book about a pet animal might also make up a story about a pet
Input.explanation_4: The location "storybook" refers to places that are imagined for the purpose of telling stories; one example of such a place is the foundation of fairytales, which is the forest.
Input.explanation_5: Usually, the fox has three colors of fur, while the fox made up of foxes in literature typically does not. Thus, the more likely place to find this specific type of fox is in a book, which contains "made up" images.

Input.question: More people should lower the guard and just have fun, we don't got long just what?
Input.answer_choices: happy, do enjoy, enjoyable, enjoy living, or get laid
Input.explanation_1: Life is short, so we should enjoy it while we can.
Input.explanation_2: Not all of us are lucky enough to have an enjoyable living, continually having fun begins to feel frivolous when it comes at the cost of time that could be spent putting in effort to obtain a life beyond the fleeting enjoyment of the moment.
Input.explanation_3: Life is an awfully short time to be living unhappily and we should all try to spend the time we have enjoying ourselves and meeting our needs rather than trying to put on a facade of nonchalance and indifference.
Input.explanation_4: It is important to enjoy living (e.g., having fun and doing things we like), rather than putting life's responsibilities and challenges always in the forefront of our mind.
Input.explanation_5: Living requires some sense of accomplishment. Although there are some moments to relax and forget about such issues (and getting some fun), many of those moments could be spent improving your life.

Input.explanation_1: If a place is hot and arid, it's likely somewhere where undeveloped land dominates the surrounding landscape, usually a desert.
Input.explanation_2: Without life present, the environment is pretty lifeless.
Input.explanation_3: A place that is hot and arid is likely to be lifeless, because it's too hot and dry for life to exist.
Input.explanation_4: People sometimes use arid to describe places that are desolate or with low humidity. Thus, an arid place would be lifeless.
Input.explanation_5: If a lifeless place is hot and arid, it must be neutral, i.e., neither cold nor hot.

Input.question: If I wanted to grow plants, where could I put a lot of dirt?

Input.explanation_3: Plants require a large amount of dirt if they are going to grow. A good place to store a lot of dirt might be a garden.

Input.explanation_5: gardening requires soil, which is dirt, and gardens are commonly put outside, not in bathrooms or within closets.

Input.question: He was very outgoing, for him making friends was no personal what?
Input.answer_choices: friendship, conflict, good feeling, scary, or having friends
Input.explanation_1: Being extroverted, one might end up in conflict with people.
Input.explanation_2: Making friends can be a conflictual process, especially if you are trying to make friends with someone who already has friends.
Input.explanation_3: For an outgoing person, making friends is no problem, e.g., for someone who loves parties, seeing new people easily, etc.
Input.explanation_4: Making friends often involves some type of conflict where two parties work to understand each other and each others' position.
Input.explanation_5: If someone was outgoing, then he or she would typically not have any conflicts.  A person who has no conflicts would not have many frightening fights, and would probably have many friends.

Input.question: I am cold, what should I do to stay warm?
Input.answer_choices: spit, light fire, lay on ice, freezer, or stay in bed
Input.explanation_1: A fire can be used to keep warm. It produces heat, and can be used to keep warm.
Input.explanation_2: It is generally wise to light a fire in the winter to keep the body warm. A fire produces heat, which contains engery which is needed to keep the body warm. Because engery circulates through the blood, the body warms up.
Input.explanation_3: Setting light to organic material, e.g., wood, heaters, and fireplaces can cause an increase in body temperature since that heat will be thermal radiation.
Input.explanation_4: It's possibly to stay warm by staying in a heated space. Fire sources have been used since immemorial times to stay warm in freezing temperatures. This includes staying inside a building which is a heated space.
Input.explanation_5: Certain body tissues, namely fat, insulate by trapping body heat. By shivering, the metabolism increases, increasing the body's ability to produce heat. Ice however is cold, decreasing the bodies ability to produce heat.

Input.explanation_5: A microscope is a device that allows one to see small objects up close.

Input.question: Where would you find the sharpest parts of a triangle?
Input.answer_choices: 3 sides, three sides, math book, three vertices, or point
Input.explanation_1: The tip of any of the sides is the sharpest part of the triangle, the tip has no curvature, so it would have to be straight up, so it would be at the vertex, of three corners.
Input.explanation_2: The sharpest parts of a triangle are the points, and so the sharpest parts of a triangle would be the vertices.
Input.explanation_3: Mathematically, this question uses the fact that three vertices define a plane, or a flat surface. Given this, the sharpest parts of the triangle would be the vertices.
Input.explanation_4: As sides of a triangle meet at vertices, and vertices can be sharp, the sharpest parts of a theoretical triangle would be the vertices of the triangle.
Input.explanation_5: Sides of a triangle are not usually sharpened. However, an obtuse or an acute triangle could be used to write with, and by sharpening the sides they would create sharper edges.

Input.explanation_1: You can catch fish and then eat them, satisfying your hunger. Thus the reason to go fishing when hungry is because you want to catch and eat fish.
Input.explanation_2: Fishing is a way to catch fish, which can be eaten.
Input.explanation_3: Catching the fish and cooking and eating them fulfills the fulfillment of hunger and fulfillment of having fun and/or getting wet.
Input.explanation_4: Fish sell for money, thus food can be bought with money, and you would want to catch some fish if you're hungry.
Input.explanation_5: Fishing can catch fish, which can substitute or complement food.

Input.question: What type of building has the most top floor?
Input.answer_choices: tall building, apartment building, go down, office building, or cabin
Input.explanation_1: Tall buildings have the most top floors, because they have the most floors.
Input.explanation_2: It's typical that tall buildings contain the most top floors. Often tall buildings are for office or hotel use, which generally have lots of workers or guesthouses, respectively. Thus tall building contain many top floors, each separated by one floor.
Input.explanation_3: Because of structural integrity, apartment buildings tend not to have the top floor occupied. Therefore, I would say, instead, that tall buildings would exist with the most top floors.
Input.explanation_4: If a tall building, a skyscraper, only has a few stories, it's likely it doesn't have a roof. Because a roof is a top floor, it must have a substantial amount of stories in order to have a top floor.
Input.explanation_5: In general, a building of a given height will have a top floor that is about the height of the first few stories. This will be followed by a floor that is half as tall as the original floor, a floor that is a third as tall

Input.question: How can someone die from eating hamburger?
Input.answer_choices: feel full, mad cow disease, death, getting full, or gas
Input.explanation_1: People (and cows) can get mad cow disease; early symptoms include difficulty swallowing, looking tired, difficulty talking, and poor coordination. If people get mad cow disease, they can die.
Input.explanation_2: Mad cow disease is a fatal disease that can be contracted by eating infected beef.
Input.explanation_3: Bacteria can be present in meat, which can be dangerous if eaten. If the person eats the meat raw, he/she could die from food poisoning. Choking is another cause of death associated with eating hamburger.
Input.explanation_4: When the cow that someone eats is infected with Mad Cow disease, that person can get Mad Cow disease and die.
Input.explanation_5: Mad cow disease is a fatal disorder of the brain. It is contracted from infected cattle and is caused by prions (infectious proteins) or cyanide gases (which may be emitted as a result of reactions related to cooking).

Input.explanation_2: The child might be able to help set the table because it would be the age where table etiquette training begins. Setting a table includes placing and filling plates and assembling silverware to which the child/child could contribute.
Input.explanation_3: Setting breakfast tables is an activity often focusing on looks and presentation, rather than function. Children trying to help would typically focus on looks, try to become adults, rather than gathering flowers carefully. Children will not likely make honey on their own.
Input.explanation_4: Setting a table is a relatively easy task that an adult may assign to a child, if the child has not been allowed to work with hot tools, sharp utensils, or dangerous chemicals.
Input.explanation_5: The child could set the table, which would help the family eat dinner.

Input.question: The victim was to take stand today, they were going to do what?
Input.answer_choices: witness, tell truth, runaway, go home, or testify
Input.explanation_1: If an defendant is on trial, there must be a number of witnesses that will testify against the defendant, testifying that they saw him or her commit some unimaginable crime.
Input.explanation_2: In a court, if a victim is to take the stand for cross-examination at a trial, they are generally going to publicly testify about what they saw.
Input.explanation_3: The victim was going to testify in court.
Input.explanation_4: The victim would be called to make a statement and answer questions. Although prosecuting and defense attorneys will weigh the depth and honesty of one's testimony, both sides can ask questions and receive truthful answers.
Input.explanation_5: A witness (i.e., one who testifies) is called to give an account of what he/she saw or heard under oath, which would occur at the stand.

Input.question: James bought a new set of tire chains and put them somewhere he could find them.  Where would he put them?
Input.answer_choices: hardware store, jewelry store, gear shift, kitchen, or garage
Input.explanation_1: People who live in areas that get a bunch of snow usually like to own chains that can be added to cars to facilitate travil on the snow. Therefore they'd keep these useful chains in the garage which is where they can most easily retrieve them.
Input.explanation_2: When one needs to put away a piece of equipment, it's useful to have a designated place to put it, as long as one knows where to find it (think "heaven and hell").
Input.explanation_3: Tire chains are used to keep tires on the road when driving in the snow. They are therefore plausable to be kept in a garage.
Input.explanation_4: He may have been able to find them later because they're not of any use until you start driving in snow, at which point the snow prevents tires from gripping the road, and tire chains can help regain traction, allowing better mobility and preventing accidents and
Input.explanation_5: People often keep spare tire chains in the garage by the side of their garage door.

Input.question: Why is it hard for a young child to read a long book?

Input.explanation_3: A young child may not be able to read many words, so a long book may be difficult to read.
Input.explanation_4: In general, stories for childern have pictures along with the words, while more complicated novels have just words on a page.
Input.explanation_5: Many children can find it tiresome to read many words without also seeing pictures that correlates to the words.

Input.explanation_5: Mechanics don't trust chickens to give them information, and so will turn to an actual, physical book of information that can teach them how to fix it.

Input.question: James found the sound relaxing.   It was so relaxing he almost did what despite his efforts?
Input.answer_choices: fall asleep, feeling good, invigorating, deep breathing, or worried
Input.explanation_1: His environment was so relaxing that he was unable to stay awake. Given this answer, other choices may include other generally feel-good related results, like feeling better, invigorating, or deep breathing, but because he still tried to fight it,
Input.explanation_2: Deep breathing is relaxing, and can cause a person to drift off to sleep.
Input.explanation_3: It can be uplifting to enjoy a relaxing sound, e.g., a kind of music, but if the relaxing sound becomes to relaxing, people may find it difficult to keep from falling asleep.
Input.explanation_4: James started to fall aslleep as he listened to the sound, even though he fought exhaustion as much as he could.
Input.explanation_5: The sound was so relaxing that it almost made James fall asleep.

Input.question: She wanted a kitten and puppy so why did she only get the puppy?
Input.answer_choices: kennel, waxy, cute, soft, or one choice for pet
Input.explanation_1: If you are only allowed to have one pet, you will probably choose the cutest one.
Input.explanation_2: Puppies generally have a waxy coating, which is thought to be cute. Cats have a coating that makes them very soft.
Input.explanation_3: A kitten is different from a puppy. One isn't better than the other, so she could only get the puppy.
Input.explanation_4: A puppy vs kitten comparison would usually involve somebody wanting both the kitten and the puppy, only being able to get one, usually the one she wanted initially, but changing her mind.
Input.explanation_5: Kittens and puppies are distinguished by one of their features, like cuteness vs. hairless.

Input.question: Where do you find the most amount of leafs?

Input.explanation_3: Leaves are found in forests.
Input.explanation_4: Ground-based plants don't produc leafs. The other four are reasonable places for leafs to be.
Input.explanation_5: Leaves are widespread in forests, often in great numbers.

Input.question: What is it called when two people in love have children?

Input.explanation_2: A main purpose of marriage, particularly in the past, was to have children. Procreation is a means to produce children.
Input.explanation_3: Procreation is the act of creating new life, and is often done by people in love.
Input.explanation_4: Pro creates new life. Procreate means to do this.
Input.explanation_5: If a couple has children then their marriage is successful. In biology procreation is the creation of offspring.

Input.question: What is main benefit to exercising?
Input.answer_choices: get in shape, weight loss, losing weight, healthy, or sweat
Input.explanation_1: From a health perspective, exercising is healthy. It increases flexibility, circulation, improves mood, burns calories, strengthens muscles, helps us sleep better, etc.
Input.explanation_2: The main benefit of exercise is that doing it usually helps you become, or stay, physically fit.
Input.explanation_3: Exercise is a way to get in shape, which is a way to improve one's physical health.
Input.explanation_4: To get in shape, work out. Exercising can help you become stronger or thinner. Exercising is sometimes done to strengthen the heart or lungs, or sweat.
Input.explanation_5: One major reason to exercise is to get healthier by becoming in shape.
